  "prompt": "How do I submit a question?",
  "response": "Submitting a question can vary depending on the platform or context you're using. Here are some general ways to submit a question:\n\n### 1. **Online Forms or Websites**\n   - Look for a \"Contact Us,\" \"FAQ,\" or \"Support\" section on the website.\n   - Fill out the provided form with your question and submit it.\n   - Some sites may also have a live chat or chatbot feature.\n\n### 2. **Email**\n   - If you have an email address for support, drafting an email with your question and sending it is a straightforward method.\n\n### 3. **Social Media**\n   - Many companies or services have social media accounts (e.g., Twitter, Facebook, Instagram). You can post your question publicly or send them a direct message.\n\n### 4. **Live Chat or Customer Support**\n   - Some websites or apps offer a live chat feature. Click on it, type your question, and wait for a response.\n\n### 5. **Forums or Communities**\n   - Platforms like Reddit, Quora, or specialized forums allow you to post questions publicly for others to answer.\n\n### 6. **Mobile Apps**\n   - If you're using an app, check for a \"Help,\" \"Support,\" or \"Ask a Question\" section.\n\n### 7. **In-Person or Over the Phone**\n   - For certain services, you might be able to call a customer support line or ask your question in person.\n\nIf you\u2019re asking how to submit a question here, simply type your question in the chat box and press \"Enter\" or click \"Send.\" I\u2019ll do my best to help!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
